BacktestingToolTemplate.name: HighYield
BacktestingToolTemplate.description:
Focuses on stocks regarded as "High Yield" with attractive valuations sorted by equal-weight ratings from all analysts. The 10 highest-ranked comprise the long portion of the portfolio, and the 10 lowest-ranked comprise the short portion. Investment is allocated using a long/short ratio of 130%/50%, with a monthly rebalance schedule.
  • Dividend Yield TTM over 3%
  • P/E under 15
  • Price over 5 USD
  • Sorted by all Analysts
  • Optimized for highest return
  • Monthly rebalance

BacktestingToolTemplate.name: Growth
BacktestingToolTemplate.description:
Focuses on stocks regarded as "Growth" with attractive valuations, sorted by equal-weight ratings from all analysts. The 10 highest-ranked comprise the long portion of the portfolio, and the 10 lowest-ranked comprise the short portion. Investment is allocated using a long/short ratio of 130%/50%, with a monthly rebalance schedule.
  • EPS Change TTM over 5%
  • P/E under 12
  • Price over 1 USD
  • Sorted by all Analysts
  • Monthly rebalance

BacktestingToolTemplate.name: Overvalued
BacktestingToolTemplate.description:
Designed to short stock that is regarded as overvalued and buy stock regarded as undervalued. The universe is sorted by market capitalization, with the 10 lowest (undervalued) stocks comprising the long portion of the portfolio, and the 10 highest (overvalued) comprising the short portion. Investment is allocated using a long/short ratio of 130%/50%, with a monthly rebalance schedule.
  • P/E over 10
  • Year To Date Change over 10%
  • Price over 5 USD
  • Sorted by Market Capitalization
  • Monthly rebalance

BacktestingToolTemplate.name: CloselyHeld
BacktestingToolTemplate.description:
Focuses on stocks with strong balance sheets and high insider ownership sorted by equal-weight ratings from all analysts. The 10 highest-ranked comprise the long portion of the portfolio, and the 10 lowest-ranked comprise the short portion. Investment is allocated using a long/short ratio of 130%/50%, with a monthly rebalance schedule.
  • LT debt/equity under 50
  • Insider Percent Owned over 20%
  • Price over 1 USD
  • Sorted by all Analysts
  • Monthly rebalance
